  <title>Cam</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>Cam (General)</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam</text> is a shape, in a moving or stationary <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> (called the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam-Part</text>) that imparts a relative motion to a different <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">part</text> (called the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Part)</text>. A <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Profile</text> is the shape help in the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Part</text> that is in continuous contact with the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam</text>. There must be relative movement between the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Cam-Part</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Follower-Part.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Follower-Profile-Shape">Follower-Shapes</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Add2DCam">Add 2D-Cam</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Add3DCam">Add 3D-Cam</link>&#32;</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
